parameters: \n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[62] As I thought, it was you... Kino.

\n<Kino>\F[62]\FF[91]\AA[FF] I wanted to talk to you
without Sawa around. Huh? Don't look so scared and
be on guard.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[62]\FF[91]\AA[F] Before we start talking, could
you please close the key to that corridor over
there? Just in case.

\n<Kino>If that caution had been displayed from the
beginning, maybe we wouldn't have ended up in this
situation, huh?

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[62]\FF[91]\AA[F] (Certainly... I have no words
to refute that)

\n<Kino>\F[62]\FF[91]\AA[FF] Well, whatever. But... I'll
make sure you can't escape while I'm not around,
okay?
!$マネージャー(座)

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[61] (Even if you go through the trouble of
moving to the bed, there's no way you can
escape...)
\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[61](However...)

When I moved to the bed... I remember the time
when Kino helped me and I accidentally touched her
skin.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[61] (It was soft... and it had a nice scent
too...)

My crotch is throbbing... but I suppose that can't
be helped. Kino, as she claims to be in charge of
visuals, has a baby face but her features are
well-proportioned. From someone's perspective, she
is quite a beautiful girl.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[61] (She used to be an underground idol... but
I discovered a strange charisma in her that was
different from Neon, so I scouted her.)

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[61] (We had a big argument back then... You
were adamant about not betraying our comrades.)

In the end, \F[61] was pushed by their comrades
and Kino ended up joining the group. And even now,
I know that they still keep in touch with their
old friends.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[61] (Of course he's angry... He's someone who
cares about his comrades more than anyone else.)
\n<Kino>\F[61]\FF[95]\AA[FF] ...Well then, shall we begin?

The sound of the door being locked behind
\F[61]\FF[95]\AA[FF] echoes in the room. A shiver
runs down my spine... That's right, this is it.

In contrast to the overwhelming performance and
beauty that attracts everyone, Neon possesses a
captivating charisma, but hers...

That unique sense of fear that she gives to
others, which is not befitting of her baby face. I
couldn't help but bow down and feel relieved, as
if I could be at ease under her captivating
charisma. She possessed that... and now, in a time
like this, I finally understand.

\n<Kino>\F[61]\FF[95]\AA[FF] I don't have any intention of
investigating you and Sawa anymore. That's a
matter between the two of you, and it's not a
problem for me, an outsider, to interfere.

\n<Kino>\F[61]\FF[95]\AA[FF] However, that is... a story
for after settling the score. I will make you pay
for the sin of making Sawa cry right here and now.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[61]\FF[95]\AA[F] Sin? What right does a traitor
like you have to say that...

\n<Kino>\F[61]\FF[95]\AA[FF] Ah, that's why... This is
also my \r[ atonement.
Kino slowly approaches as they say that.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[61]\FF[95]\AA[F] (What the hell... What do you
intend to do to me? Don't tell me you're going to
kill me... Ugh! Run--...)

Due to fear, my body trembles and stiffens. In
addition, my limbs are numb, and I am completely
embodying the situation of a frog being stared at
by a snake.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(I-I have no choice but to persuade... Damn it...
If necessary, even beg for my life...)

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[61]\FF[95]\AA[F] Wait a minute! It's a bit
exaggerated to make such a big deal out of just
using Sawa's mouth...

\n<Kino>\F[61]\FF[95]\AA[FF] Did you use it...? Perhaps
Sawa wasn't crying because she was used, but
because you ended up becoming like that...

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[61]\FF[95]\AA[F] (Tch... Is this backfiring?!
Damn it, I won't die in a place like this!!)

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[61]\FF[95]\AA[FF] W-Wait... Please don't kill
me...

\n<Kino>\F[61]\FF[95]\AA[FF] That's so disgusting... I
didn't want to see you like that...

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[61]\FF[95]\AA[FF] (T-This is no good... He's
completely lost his mind... No matter what I
say...)

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[62]\FF[93]\AA[F] (There's a small key \C[2]...
I've been curious about this for a while...)
\n<Sawa>\F[62]\FF[93]\AA[FF] ...Is it a key?

\n<Sonoda Kohei>\F[62]\FF[93]\AA[F] I thought it would be bad to
take it without permission, so I left it alone...
Well... I have a master key too, so either way, I
don't need it...
